{
  "texts": [
    "For any L-biLipschitz h: [0, 1] d → ℓ 2, there exists a rectangle R ∈ R ≤k 0 such that R does not have φ-property 2.Proof.",
    "Let k 0 ∈ N be such that (1 + φ) k 0 ≥ L 2.",
    "Suppose, for contradiction, that every rectangle R ∈ R ≤k 0 has φ-property 2.",
    "Then, by definition, we find a sequence of rectanglesR 1, R 2,..., R k 0, each R k ∈ R k with R 0 ⊃ R 1 ⊃ R 2 ⊃ • • • ⊃ R k 0 and such that A h (R k) > (1 + φ)A h (R k-1) for each k = 1, 2,..., k 0.",
    "Thus, A h (R k 0) > (1 + φ) k 0 A h (R 0) ≥ (1 + φ) k 0 1 L. Since A h (R k 0) ≤ L, this implies L > (1 + φ) k 0 1 L,which contradicts the choice of k 0.Corollary 5.16."
  ]
}